@milas Thank for another Pull request that adds really useful functionality!

I have a proposition how to implement this feature in a little bit less invasive way.
We try to separate concerns in our software as much as possible.
I think that `ApiModel` shouldn't care about (serialization/ deserialization) of attributes.

### Structure
Here is my idea how we can achieve this functionality only modifying the `AttributeField`:
```python
class AttributeField(BaseField):
    def __init__(self, source):
        self.source = source

    def __get__(self, instance, type=None):
        if instance is None:
            return self
        else:
            value = instance.attributes[self.source]
            return self.deserialize(value)

    def __set__(self, instance, value):
        serialized_value = self.serialize(value)
        instance.attributes[self.source] = serialized_value
        
    def deserialize(self, value):
        return value

    def serialize(self, value):
        return value
```

### Custom Attribute Fields
This way defining your own field type is as easy as subclassing `AttributeField`:
```python
class UuidField(AttributeField):
    def deserialize(self, value):
        return uuid.UUID(value)

    def serialize(self, value):
        return str(value)
```

### Caching
I thing that caching is not necessary in this stage of development of jsonapi-requests.
Caching should be left for clients of the library.
However by adding `deserialize` and `serialize`, adding cache is easy, you just have to:
```python
class UuidField(AttributeField):
    @functools.lru_cahe()
    def deserialize(self, value):
        return uuid.UUID(value)

    @functools.lru_cahe()
    def serialize(self, value):
        return str(value)
```

You could even share the one cache for all instances of Custom field:
```python
class UuidField(AttributeField):
    @functools.lru_cahe()
    @staticmethod
    def deserialize(value):
        return uuid.UUID(value)

    @functools.lru_cahe()
    @staticmethod
    def serialize(value):
        return str(value)
```

