@cpcloud Yep, updating to Pandas 0.17 definitely fixes the issue.

It comes down to `pd.to_datetime(' ', errors='ignore')` returning `' '` in 0.17, whereas in 0.16 `pd.to_datetime(' ') == datetime(2015, 10, 23)` during odo's type discovery.  When reading in the whole file, then, Pandas has to do datetime parsing on that last fake column, which is hundreds of times slower, overall.

So I'm not sure what the best route is -- should I continue to work on this fix, or should we just make odo depend on pandas 0.17?  How far back in pandas versions do we support?

